1
00:00:18,580 --> 00:00:21,420
♪Wearing peach blossom makeup,
I boil tea over the stove♪

2
00:00:23,060 --> 00:00:25,780
♪With a pure heart,
I embroider the brocade of time♪

3
00:00:27,380 --> 00:00:31,380
♪On the short paper,
affection flows in the silent moonlight♪

4
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:34,940
♪I only wish that by my side,
is my love♪

5
00:00:36,820 --> 00:00:39,940
♪Cool autumn wind blowing,
I gaze far leaning against the railing♪

6
00:00:41,620 --> 00:00:44,460
♪Sunset glow over the green hill,
in formation wild geese are flying♪

7
00:00:45,940 --> 00:00:50,020
♪Covering a thousand miles on horseback,
for whom is he longing♪

8
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:53,620
♪He returned home in dreams♪

9
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:58,220
♪I will never forget
that you held my hands♪

10
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:03,020
♪In your warm palms
and we braved winds and waves♪

11
00:01:03,260 --> 00:01:08,300
♪Unexpectedly, after we traveled so far
and turned grey-haired♪

12
00:01:08,580 --> 00:01:12,260
♪I am still by your side♪

13
00:01:12,540 --> 00:01:16,820
♪Hearts burning,
we look into each other's eyes♪

14
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:21,500
♪Feelings overflowing,
they don't need to be hided♪

15
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:26,500
♪No matter how time passes
and life changes♪

16
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:31,060
♪Together, we will grow old♪

17
00:01:32,140 --> 00:01:36,180
=The Sword and the Brocade=

18
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:39,580
=Episode 22=

19
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:42,480
Red cymbidium is rare.

20
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:45,480
But people with ulterior motivations

21
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,960
are not rare.

22
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,560
Orchid is a noble plant.

23
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,400
Not everyone is qualified

24
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:53,080
to comment on it.

25
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:54,560
If it falls into

26
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,320
the filthy hands,

27
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,840
its nobleness

28
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:00,040
will be defiled.

29
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:16,200
I heard that quite a few bad things

30
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,280
have happened to Ou family recently.

31
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:22,840
Young Madam Ou,
you must've had a hard time.

32
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,440
The banquet will begin soon.

33
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,600
Let's go.

34
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:46,840
Let's go.

35
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:00,140
(Kindness Brings in Fortune)

36
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,120
What a big feast.

37
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,480
Here, take a seat.

38
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:15,920
Great Madam Xu, you are here.

39
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:18,880
-Madam Tang.
-Please.

40
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:22,840
Madam Tang,

41
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,280
thank you for inviting us.

42
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,200
I hope

43
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:28,000
you'll like the food.

44
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,440
They are all nice dishes.

45
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,000
-Here.
-Let's sit down.

46
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,080
-Sit.
-The dishes smell and look so good.

47
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:40,480
Hope you'll enjoy the food.

48
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,360
-How have you been doing?
-Good.

49
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:45,640
You look so good today.

50
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:46,800
-Not bad.
-Thank you.

51
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,440
Young Madam Ou, you are here.

52
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,040
Daughter, come here

53
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,440
and greet the madam.

54
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,240
Please sit down.

55
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,200
Young Madam Wang.

56
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,760
Thank you.

57
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,270
I'm in good health.

58
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:16,720
-Everything's fine.
-Sure.

59
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,320
Yes.

60
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,560
It looks so nice.

61
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:31,360
Now, let's eat.

62
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,320
-Okay.
-Okay.

63
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,800
Great Madam Zheng, try this.

64
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,280
This looks good.

65
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:50,800
Erniang, how have you been doing?

66
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,680
I've been doing very well.

67
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,080
You should mind your own business.

68
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,960
Why do you care about me?

69
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,800
Just enjoy being
the wife of the Marquis.

70
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,240
Erniang.

71
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,760
Here, taste this.

72
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:12,400
Okay.

73
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:15,560
What happened to you?

74
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,440
It's none of your business.

75
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,160
Erniang.

76
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,720
Erniang.

77
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:25,800
Erniang.

78
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:27,880
What happened?

79
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,400
How did your wrist get hurt?

80
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:37,200
Look. There are wounds everywhere.

81
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,440
Are you happy now?

82
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,600
Wang Yu hit you?

83
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:43,880
How dare he treat you like that?

84
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:46,160
Why didn't you tell us earlier?

85
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,440
Tell you?

86
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:50,040
Don't pretend anymore.

87
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,960
If you hadn't replaced me
to marry the Marquis,

88
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:54,320
I wouldn't have ended up like this.

89
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,440
I replaced you?

90
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,320
Do you know

91
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,120
why my mother would go

92
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,640
to Ci'an Temple on that day?

93
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,280
Because I was going to
run away from the wedding.

94
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:10,440
Hadn't you set up a trap for me

95
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,040
and asked Madam Wang to keep me home,

96
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,640
we would've left
the capital long time ago.

97
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:15,480
In that case,

98
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,720
you could've married

99
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,920
into Xu family,

100
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,640
and my mother wouldn't have been...

101
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,360
What?

102
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,680
You mean back then...

103
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,120
You mean you wanted to...

104
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,360
You wanted to run away
from the wedding?

105
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:37,360
No.

106
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:38,840
I don't believe you.

107
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:40,640
You are lying.

108
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,360
There's no way that you didn't

109
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,840
want to marry the Marquis.

110
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,400
How could I use

111
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:46,080
my mother's death to lie to you?

112
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,640
Erniang, think about it.

113
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,320
Have I ever fought you

114
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,040
over anything since we were little?

115
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,440
I just wanted to marry into
a wealthy family.

116
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:00,720
I just wanted to live with pride

117
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:03,040
for the rest of my life.

118
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,280
What have I done wrong?

119
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,600
Why do I have to end up like this?

120
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:23,760
Erniang,

121
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,720
just let bygone

122
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,280
be bygone.

123
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,040
Where there's a will, there's a way.

124
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,960
Our fates are

125
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,920
in our own hands.

126
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,360
That's right.

127
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:54,200
You look so much better lately.

128
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:54,880
Yes.

129
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,920
So do you.

130
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:59,280
Has she visited you?

131
00:07:59,320 --> 00:07:59,840
Yes.

132
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:00,680
How did it come out?

133
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,040
Very nice.

134
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:07,760
Is it okay?

135
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:09,680
Yes. Very pretty.

136
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,360
Madam Xu.

137
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,560
Young Madam Ou.

138
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,200
I notice that the embroidery
on your cuffs

139
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,320
is quite unusual.

140
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:22,000
Would you mind me asking

141
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,760
where you got it?

142
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,800
Just some embroidery.

143
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:29,120
Why are you so curious, Madam Xu?

144
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:30,720
Please don't get me wrong.

145
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,640
I learned embroidery for a few years.

146
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,030
So when I see something new,

147
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,320
it makes me interested.

148
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:37,120
Madam Xu, you have quite a taste.

149
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,080
The embroidery on
Young Madam Ou's clothes

150
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,640
is indeed rarely seen in the capital.

151
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,240
We all envy her.

152
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:44,320
No need to envy.

153
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:45,720
Our fabric

154
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:46,440
is all brought back

155
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,880
by Zunzhang from the south.

156
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,000
If you like it,

157
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,640
I'll give you some tomorrow.

158
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,320
Then I'll thank you in advance,
Young Madam Ou.

159
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,480
You are welcome.

160
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,480
The embroidery is surely different,

161
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,840
but I'm so tired of looking at it.

162
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,280
I do wanna try

163
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,800
something else.

164
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,640
The ladies I know

165
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,400
are all frequent customers
of Xianling Pavilion.

166
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:07,200
It's said that Master Jian
of Xianling Pavilion

167
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,800
has excellent embroidery skills.

168
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:11,280
Xianling Pavilion?

169
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,640
I've heard of it.

170
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,780
(Duke Mao's Mansion)

171
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,320
Dear,

172
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,880
what are you looking for?

173
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:46,880
Where are you going with the money?

174
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:49,040
Young Madam.

175
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:51,000
You think you can stop me?

176
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:52,440
Dear.

177
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:55,040
(Erniang,)

178
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:58,360
(just let bygone be bygone.)

179
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,440
(Where there's a will, there's a way.)

180
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,680
(Our fates are)

181
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:03,920
(in our own hands.)

182
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:09,880
Dear,

183
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,240
I lied to you before.

184
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,280
It's my bad.

185
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,520
I know I was wrong.

186
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,920
I promise I'll serve you well
in the future.

187
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,680
Let's start over

188
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,560
and live a good life together,

189
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,200
okay?

190
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,040
Live a good life?

191
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,160
Sure.

192
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,040
As long as you let me have Baizhi,

193
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:43,360
I'll give you a good life.

194
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,640
Dear.

195
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,680
Baizhi has got engaged.

196
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:54,280
She'll get married next month.

197
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,680
I can't do that to her.

198
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:57,880
Dear.

199
00:10:58,640 --> 00:10:59,600
Father

200
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,680
punished you because

201
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,360
you raped a girl.

202
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,200
If Father gets mad at you again

203
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,880
because of this,

204
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,000
you'll be in trouble.

205
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,200
Don't try to scare me with my father.

206
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:14,400
You can't even do this for me,

207
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,280
and you want a good life?

208
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:23,320
Young Madam.

209
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:26,200
What should we do, Young Madam?

210
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,680
Don't be afraid.

211
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:33,080
Just wait till next month
and get married.

212
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:34,960
I won't

213
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,200
put you in misery.

214
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:39,920
Young Madam.

215
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,520
Shiyi,

216
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,760
you are wrong.

217
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,640
It's the way it is now.

218
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,920
Nothing can be changed.

219
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,600
Don't. Don't.

220
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:16,480
My Lord.

221
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,800
How much did His Lordship drink?

222
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,160
Don't ask. Just get him back first.

223
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:20,560
My Lord.

224
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:22,920
Let's go.

225
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,200
Come on.

226
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:26,760
Hold on. Hold it.

227
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:27,400
Where are you going?

228
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,320
Back to Banyuepan.

229
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:30,960
Look.

230
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:31,720
His Lordship is so drunk.

231
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:32,760
Why take him back to Banyuepan?

232
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:34,720
General, you are indeed wise.

233
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:35,400
Let's go.

234
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,360
The Western Lateral Court is this way.

235
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,200
Come on.

236
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,480
This fan is so pretty.

237
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:43,000
That's right.

238
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:43,800
Look

239
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:46,920
how shiny and colorful it is.

240
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:50,480
Don't.

241
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,240
My Lord.

242
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,440
What happened to him?

243
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:53,520
Your Ladyship, don't worry.

244
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,440
His Lordship had a drink
with a few friends

245
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:56,480
and he got a little drunk.

246
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:57,440
He just needs some rest.

247
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:59,240
But why do you bring him here?

248
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,600
His Lordship is drunk like this.

249
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:01,480
We think that it's

250
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:02,240
better for Your Ladyship

251
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,280
to take care of him.

252
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,080
Thank you, Your Ladyship.

253
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:06,720
Don't. Don't. Don't.

254
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:07,600
Your Ladyship,

255
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,840
we'll take off now.

256
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:10,200
Your Ladyship,

257
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:10,960
I'll go boil some water.

258
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:11,800
I'll go chop firewood.

259
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:14,160
Don't. Dongqing. Amber.

260
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,240
My Lord.

261
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,160
How is...

262
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,520
Don't... Don't.

263
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,440
My Lord. I...

264
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:29,160
Put me on the bed.

265
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,000
Go over there.

266
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:37,360
I'll go boil some water.

267
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:38,280
You stay here.

268
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,120
I'll go prepare His Lordship's

269
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,320
clothes for tomorrow.

270
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,560
What are you doing, General Fu?

271
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,040
Don't hit me so hard.

272
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:55,480
It's late already. Won't you go back?

273
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,200
His Lordship will
finally sleep here tonight.

274
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,360
Aren't you curious?

275
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,040
Why would I be curious about
my masters' matter?

276
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,920
I'm a disciplined maid.

277
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:20,640
Okay. Alright.

278
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:21,880
You are so heavy.

279
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:25,200
Don't move.

280
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:26,840
You...

281
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:28,920
My Lord. My Lord.

282
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,920
Don't move.

283
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,040
Let me clean your face.

284
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:47,880
